xbrlcore.taxonomy
Class DiscoverableTaxonomySet

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.taxonomy.DiscoverableTaxonomySet
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class DiscoverableTaxonomySet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class represents a discoverable taxonomy set (DTS).

A DTS consists of mulitple taxonomies, which themselves consist of a (taxonomy) schema file and different linkbases. For DTS rules of discovery, see XBRL Spec. section 3.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

getConceptByID

public Concept getConceptByID(java.lang.String id)
Returns a Concept object to a specific ID from the DTS. All the taxonomies belonging to this DTS are scanned for the element.

Parameters:
id - The ID for which the element shall be obtained.
Returns:
